.TH "ext2_splice_branch" 9 "ext2_splice_branch" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ext2_splice_branch \- splice the allocated branch onto inode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ext2_splice_branch
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "long block "  ","
.BI "Indirect *where "  ","
.BI "int num "  ","
.BI "int blks "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
owner
.IP "block" 12
(logical) number of block we are adding
.IP "where" 12
location of missing link
.IP "num" 12
number of indirect blocks we are adding
.IP "blks" 12
number of direct blocks we are adding
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function fills the missing link and does all housekeeping needed in
inode (->i_blocks, etc.). In case of success we end up with the full
chain to new block and return 0.
